# Design System Domino Chain

Always use design system classes for web pages. Do not write custom HTML/CSS outside the design system.

## Page Structure

### Standard Pages (outside beta area)

```erb
<div class="ds-page">
  <div class="ds-container">
    <header class="ds-header">
      <%= image_tag "domino-chain-logo.png", alt: "Domino Chain", class: "ds-header-logo", width: 48, height: 48 %>
      <h1 class="ds-title">Title</h1>
      <p class="ds-subtitle">Subtitle</p>
    </header>
    <!-- content -->
  </div>
</div>
```

### Beta Area (layout `beta_dashboard`)

- The layout provides the **sidebar** (`ds-beta-sidebar`, `ds-beta-nav-link`, etc.) and the main area (`ds-beta-main-inner`).
- Each beta view should include: `content_for :title`, an optional **page header** (`ds-beta-page-head`, `ds-beta-page-title`, `ds-beta-page-lead`), then content using DS components below (`ds-beta-section`, `ds-beta-control-card`, DS forms).
- Do not wrap the full `yield` in `ds-page` / `ds-container`: those classes are for non-beta layout pages.

## Components

- **Buttons**: `ds-btn ds-btn--primary` | `ds-btn--secondary` | `ds-btn--ghost` (+ `ds-btn--sm` for small buttons)
- **Forms**: `ds-form`, `ds-form-group`, `ds-form-label`, `ds-input`, `ds-textarea`
- **Flash**: `ds-flash ds-flash--success` | `ds-flash--error`
- **Sections**: `ds-section-title` for section titles
- **Badges / statuses**: `ds-badge`, `ds-status` + variants (`--on`, `--off`, `--pending`, `--error`, `--locked`)
- **Toggles**: use `ds-toggle` (or DS components that embed it, e.g. `ds-beta-catalog-toggle-*`)
- **Action links**: use `ds-btn` rather than custom styles

## Colors / Tokens

- Current palette: `magenta` (primary CTA + secondary outline + toggles/check/radio), `blue` (accent, links, focus), `violet` (special states), `error`.
- Legacy aliases `amber`/`teal` remain allowed for compatibility, but do not introduce new names outside DS tokens.
- Always consume DS variables/tokens, never hardcode hex values in views/feature SCSS.

## Web Logos / Favicons

- The layout must reference assets from `backend/public/favicons/` + `backend/public/icon.svg`.
- Do not reintroduce icon/favicon files outside these paths without coordinated branding doc updates.

